$DGXX f you're up 100% on this stock, sell and cash out. Don't be greedy. This stock is way over bought and over valued for its fundamentals. It has low revenues and negative earnings. Everything has to go just right to justify these prices. And they've been tapping the ATM every time the SP goes up. 
 
 
As for the Peter Griffin and Citadel angle, their investment in this company is a drop in the bucket compared with their vast holdings. They do this with many many small companies, hoping a couple will catch fire and establish themselves, and make up for the rest. 
 
 
DGXX has potential, 1-2 years out. And that's it. Keep a small position and wait it out. 
 
 
And don't forget, AI and the stock market are in a bubble. Could crash anytime. There's a reason why Warren Buffet is selling.
